defs.docs: Simple time handling.

defs.name: Duration
defs.docs:
ISO 8601 time duration with nanosecond precision.
 This also allows for the negative duration; see individual methods for details.

defs.name: weeks
defs.docs:
Makes a new `Duration` with given number of weeks.
 Equivalent to `Duration::seconds(weeks * 7 * 24 * 60 * 60)` with overflow checks.
 Panics when the duration is out of bounds.

defs.name: days
defs.docs:
Makes a new `Duration` with given number of days.
 Equivalent to `Duration::seconds(days * 24 * 60 * 60)` with overflow checks.
 Panics when the duration is out of bounds.

defs.name: hours
defs.docs:
Makes a new `Duration` with given number of hours.
 Equivalent to `Duration::seconds(hours * 60 * 60)` with overflow checks.
 Panics when the duration is out of bounds.

defs.name: minutes
defs.docs:
Makes a new `Duration` with given number of minutes.
 Equivalent to `Duration::seconds(minutes * 60)` with overflow checks.
 Panics when the duration is out of bounds.

defs.name: seconds
defs.docs:
Makes a new `Duration` with given number of seconds.
 Panics when the duration is more than `i64::MAX` milliseconds
 or less than `i64::MIN` milliseconds.

defs.name: milliseconds
defs.docs: Makes a new `Duration` with given number of milliseconds.

defs.name: microseconds
defs.docs: Makes a new `Duration` with given number of microseconds.

defs.name: nanoseconds
defs.docs: Makes a new `Duration` with given number of nanoseconds.

defs.name: span
defs.docs:
Runs a closure, returning the duration of time it took to run the
 closure.

defs.name: num_weeks
defs.docs: Returns the total number of whole weeks in the duration.

defs.name: num_days
defs.docs: Returns the total number of whole days in the duration.

defs.name: num_hours
defs.docs: Returns the total number of whole hours in the duration.

defs.name: num_minutes
defs.docs: Returns the total number of whole minutes in the duration.

defs.name: num_seconds
defs.docs: Returns the total number of whole seconds in the duration.

defs.name: num_milliseconds
defs.docs: Returns the total number of whole milliseconds in the duration,

defs.name: num_microseconds
defs.docs:
Returns the total number of whole microseconds in the duration,
 or `None` on overflow (exceeding 2<sup>63</sup> microseconds in either direction).

defs.name: num_nanoseconds
defs.docs:
Returns the total number of whole nanoseconds in the duration,
 or `None` on overflow (exceeding 2<sup>63</sup> nanoseconds in either direction).

defs.name: checked_add
defs.docs: Add two durations, returning `None` if overflow occurred.

defs.name: checked_sub
defs.docs: Subtract two durations, returning `None` if overflow occurred.

defs.name: min_value
defs.docs: The minimum possible `Duration`: `i64::MIN` milliseconds.

defs.name: max_value
defs.docs: The maximum possible `Duration`: `i64::MAX` milliseconds.

defs.name: zero
defs.docs: A duration where the stored seconds and nanoseconds are equal to zero.

defs.name: is_zero
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the duration equals `Duration::zero()`.

Represents error when converting `Duration` to/from a standard library
 implementation

defs.name: strptime
defs.docs: Parses the time from the string according to the format string.

defs.name: Timespec
defs.docs:
A record specifying a time value in seconds and nanoseconds, where
 nanoseconds represent the offset from the given second.

defs.name: get_time
defs.docs:
Returns the current time as a `timespec` containing the seconds and
 nanoseconds since 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z.

defs.name: precise_time_ns
defs.docs:
Returns the current value of a high-resolution performance counter
 in nanoseconds since an unspecified epoch.

defs.name: precise_time_s
defs.docs:
Returns the current value of a high-resolution performance counter
 in seconds since an unspecified epoch.

defs.name: PreciseTime
defs.docs: An opaque structure representing a moment in time.

defs.name: now
defs.docs: Returns a `PreciseTime` representing the current moment in time.

defs.name: to
defs.docs:
Returns a `Duration` representing the span of time from the value of
 `self` to the value of `later`.

defs.name: SteadyTime
defs.docs: A structure representing a moment in time.

defs.name: now
defs.docs: Returns a `SteadyTime` representing the current moment in time.

defs.name: Tm
defs.value: Tm { tm_sec, tm_min, tm_hour, tm_mday, tm_mon, tm_year, tm_wday, tm_yday, tm_isdst, tm_utcoff, tm_nsec }
defs.docs:
Holds a calendar date and time broken down into its components (year, month,
 day, and so on), also called a broken-down time value.

defs.name: tm_sec
defs.docs: Seconds after the minute - [0, 60]

defs.name: tm_min
defs.docs: Minutes after the hour - [0, 59]

defs.name: tm_hour
defs.docs: Hours after midnight - [0, 23]

defs.name: tm_mday
defs.docs: Day of the month - [1, 31]

defs.name: tm_mon
defs.docs: Months since January - [0, 11]

defs.name: tm_year
defs.docs: Years since 1900

defs.name: tm_wday
defs.docs: Days since Sunday - [0, 6]. 0 = Sunday, 1 = Monday, ..., 6 = Saturday.

defs.name: tm_yday
defs.docs: Days since January 1 - [0, 365]

defs.name: tm_isdst
defs.docs: Daylight Saving Time flag.

defs.name: tm_utcoff
defs.docs:
Identifies the time zone that was used to compute this broken-down time
 value, including any adjustment for Daylight Saving Time. This is the
 number of seconds east of UTC. For example, for U.S. Pacific Daylight
 Time, the value is `-7*60*60 = -25200`.

defs.name: tm_nsec
defs.docs: Nanoseconds after the second - [0, 10<sup>9</sup> - 1]
